Charles Czeisler, a professor of sleep medicine at Harvard Medical School and specialist at Brigham and Women's Hospital, is the one who created the course, which is believed to be the first of its kind in the US.
It was inspired to create the course after holding a conference about the impact of lack of sleep on the ability to learn.
“In the end, a girl came and said to me, «Why am I being told this only now, in the last year?»
