Foreign buyers will be charged a higher stamp court fee when buying a property in the United Kingdom
Foreign buyers will pay a higher stamp court fee when buying property in the United Kingdom, with additional money to be used to help homeless people, according to the Conservative Party's new plans
This change will neutralize the success of Corbyn's efforts to attract young people with voting rights
