Treasury expects to raise up to £120 million a year for homelessness relief
Foreign buyers will be charged a higher stamp court fee when buying a property in the United Kingdom, and additional money will be used to help homeless people, as Theresa May is expected to announce today.
The change will be considered an attempt to neutralize the success of Jeremy Corbyn's efforts to attract young people with voting rights, promising more advantageous homes and targeting high-income people.
The higher stamp court fee will be applied to individuals and legal entities who are not taxpayers in the United Kingdom, and the additional money thus obtained will be used to support the Government's efforts to help homeless people.
