The new policy comes just weeks after Boris Johnson called for a stamp court fee cut to help young people buy their first home.
It accused large construction firms of maintaining high prices on property as a result of land purchase without using it, however, and asked Theresa May to waive taxes on affordable homes, with a view to resolving the UK "house issue".
